    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Deed books, 1761-1770, of Halifax County Court. The deed books record the name of the grantor and grantee, the residence of both individuals and the description of property being sold or transferred. Deed book,
No. 3, 1761-1762 has a poll list related to a House of Burgess election. Deed books, Nos. 3 and 5 have indexes which contains the first and last names of both parties. It is arranged alphabetically from A-Z. Deed
books, Nos. 6 and 7 do not have indexes.
</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement>
      <head>Arrangement
